race.comment: BOLDINHO (1) keeps winning comfortably for the top stable (Clarke) and carries weight. Has been backed off the map his last three, and it's hard to go past him again. PEEL THE STICKERS (5) switched from a Victorian barn and went close first-up in a 76. Has 3kg weight relief and has won second-up. Suited over the longer sprint and is certainly good enough at best. Keep very safe. Stablemate CONVINCEBILITY (2) was tracking well before a plain effort last time. Maps well and also carries 3kg less. Has to be considered. AWASH (3) has to drop back from the mile, but he always puts in and should be around the mark.
